Package: FADN2Footprint
Type: Package
Title: Infer agricultural practices and compute environmental footprints from FADN data.
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Sarah", "Huet", email = "sarah.huet@inrae.fr",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
URL: https://sarah-huet.github.io/FADN2Footprint/, https://github.com/sarah-huet/FADN2Footprint
BugReports: https://github.com/sarah-huet/FADN2Footprint/issues
Description: Infers agricultural practices and computes environmental footprints
    from Farm Accountancy Data Network (FADN) data.
    The package supports two input configurations: national
    FADN combined with national Land Parcel Identification System (LPIS),
    hedges and cover crop maps; or European Union FADN data.
    Additional internal data sets include farm practices surveys,
    feed composition tables, and parameters from national greenhouse gas
    inventories or Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) guidelines.
    Following a life cycle assessment approach (scope 3), it derives farm practices
    (fertilizer use, pesticides, tillage, crop diversity, hedge density, 
    field size, ground cover, livestock density, feed intake,
    rearing parameters, manure management, animal weight) and estimates
    environmental footprints (greenhouse gas emissions, biodiversity
    impact, water consumption and pollution). Results
    are estimated at farm, activity, and product level.
